---
source: tests/help.rs
expression: "help(&[\"validate\", \"--help\"])"
---
Check OKF conformance: report unparseable, untyped, or malformed docs

Usage: okq validate [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --bundle <DIR>
          Bundle directory to query [default: current directory]

      --check
          Exit 3 if the bundle is not conformant (any error). For CI gating

      --json
          Emit machine-readable JSON on stdout instead of human-readable text

      --severity <LEVEL>
          Minimum severity to display

          Possible values:
          - error:   Conformance errors only
          - warning: Warnings and errors (default)
          - info:    Everything, including info-level findings (e.g. unresolved links)
          
          [default: warning]

      --no-color
          Disable colored output (also honors NO_COLOR)

      --no-ignore
          Ignore all .okqignore files; query the full tree, nothing excluded

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

Examples:
  # Full conformance report (errors + warnings)
  okq validate

  # Same command, friendlier name
  okq doctor

  # Fail CI if the bundle is not conformant (any error)
  okq validate --check

  # Include info-level findings (e.g. unresolved links), as JSON
  okq validate --severity info --json
